ents. Author Cho Haejin weaves these characters into a story of hope and trust, one that asks basic questions about what it means to be human and humane.First published in 2011 in South Korea, this timely and moving story won the 2013 Shin Dong-yup Prize for Literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aKoreanszBelgiumvFiction. 0aPolitical refugeeszKorea (North)vFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aFulton, Bruce, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLee, Ji-Eun.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065814940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780824880408zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824880408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824880408/original  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065814-9  University of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-al